article.headline: Tennessee Tech 72, S. Utah 65
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- Frank Davis had 19 points to lead Tennessee Tech to a 72-65 victory over Southern Utah Wednesday night. Elijah Muhammad had 12 points and Alfred Jones added 11 points and nine rebounds for the Golden Eagles (3-3). Davis Baker had a game-high 25 points and seven rebounds to lead the Thunderbirds (3-3). Matt Hodsgon added 12 points and Ryan Brimley had 11. Southern Utah outscored Tennessee Tech 37-36 in the second half, but it wasn't enough to compensate for a 36-28 halftime deficit. After making 4 of 8 from 3-point range in the first half, the Eagles sunk just 1 of 5 in the second.
